     Committee on Ways and Means
              107th Congress, Committee Rules and Jurisdiction

     The Committee Rules (WMCP 107-1, PDF)  for the 107th Congress were
   adopted by the Committee in its organizational meeting on February 7,
   2001.
     * The Committee's jurisdiction and history briefly describes the
       Committee's rich history and outlines its legislative jurisdiction.
       A description of the jurisdiction of the Subcommittees follows:
          + Subcommittee on Trade
          + Subcommittee on Oversight
          + Subcommittee on Health
          + Subcommittee on Social Security
          + Subcommittee on Human Resources
          + Subcommittee on Select Revenue Measures

